<h1>
    Club Welfare Page
</h1>
<p>
    At Tiverton Water Polo Club, the safety, well-being, and happiness of our members are of utmost importance.
    We are committed to providing a safe and inclusive environment for everyone to enjoy the sport of water polo.
    This page serves as a resource to inform our members, parents, and guardians about our welfare policies, procedures, and contacts.
</p>
<h2>
    Our Commitment to Welfare
</h2>
<p>
    We are a Swim England registered water polo club, and as such, we adhere to the highest standards of welfare and
    child protection. Our club is dedicated to creating an atmosphere where all participants, regardless of age, gender,
    race, or ability, can thrive in a secure and respectful setting.
</p>
<h2>
    Welfare Officers
</h2>
<p>
    Our club has an appointed Welfare Officer who is responsible for promoting and safeguarding the welfare of all our members.
    They are available to offer guidance, support, and assistance to anyone who has concerns related to welfare issues. Our Welfare
    Officer can be reached via email or phone, and their contact details can be found below:
</p>
