<p>
    Our club follows Swim England's safeguarding policies, which encompass guidelines on appropriate behavior, anti-bullying measures,
    and the importance of creating a safe online environment. We have a Code of Conduct that outlines our expectations for players,
    coaches, parents, and spectators to ensure a respectful and inclusive atmosphere at all times.
</p>
<h2>
    Reporting Concerns
</h2>
<p>
    If you have any concerns related to welfare, child protection, or any other issue within the club, which can not be resolved by one of our coaches,
    we encourage you to reach out to our Welfare Officer. They are here to listen, offer support, and take appropriate action as necessary.
    If you believe a child is in immediate danger, please contact the local authorities or emergency services.
</p>
